Example stanfit object

Source: R/data.R
sample_stanfit.Rd

An example stanfit object following the example fit of a heirarchical schools model from the pystan documentation. 'https://pystan.readthedocs.io/en/latest/'.

sample_stanfit

Format

A stanfit object with 18 parameters, 3 chains, 10000 iterations and 500 warmup samples

Examples

# show model used to create sample
sample_stanfit@stanmodel

#> S4 class stanmodel 'fa9422f5ae55af63144368ec85d72c15' coded as follows:
#> data {
#>             int<lower=0> J; // number of schools
#>             real y[J]; // estimated treatment effects
#>             real<lower=0> sigma[J]; // s.e. of effect estimates
#>           }
#>           parameters {
#>             real mu;
#>             real<lower=0> tau;
#>             real eta[J];
#>           }
#>           transformed parameters {
#>             real theta[J];
#>             for (j in 1:J)
#>             theta[j] = mu + tau * eta[j];
#>           }
#>           model {
#>             target += normal_lpdf(eta | 0, 1);
#>             target += normal_lpdf(y | theta, sigma);
#>           } 
# print model summary
sample_stanfit
